The absence of uterus suggests Müllerian duct agenesis, which is a congenital disorder in which the Müllerian ducts fail to develop, resulting in absence of uterus and upper vagina. 17-alpha-hydroxylase enzyme deficiency is a rare form of congenital adrenal hyperplasia that results in hypertension, ambiguous external genitalia, and lack of secondary sexual characteristics. Androgen insensitivity and pure gonadal dysgenesis are both conditions that can lead to incomplete or absent female puberty, but they typically do not result in the complete absence of a uterus.
